@* ===== ABOUT THE PROJECT ===== *@
<MudText Typo="Typo.h4" Class="mb-2" Style="font-weight: 700;">
    <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Info" Class="mr-2" Style="vertical-align: middle;" />
    About the Project
</MudText>
<MudDivider Class="mb-4" />

<MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4" Style="line-height: 1.9; text-align: justify;">
    The <strong>Academic Management System (AMS)</strong> module is a core component of the College Management System (CMS).
    This module is specifically designed to manage and automate academic-related processes within the institution.
    While CMS handles multiple institutional operations, the AMS module focuses exclusively on academic workflow management.

    The AMS module includes <strong>student enrollment management</strong>,
    <strong>course and curriculum configuration</strong>,
    <strong>semester and batch management</strong>,
    <strong>faculty allocation</strong>,
    <strong>timetable scheduling</strong>,
    <strong>attendance tracking</strong>, and
    <strong>examination and result processing</strong>.

    The module operates under a structured <strong>Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)</strong> mechanism,
    ensuring that Administrator, Faculty, Principal, and Student roles access only authorized academic features.
    The architecture follows a clean layered design to ensure scalability, maintainability,
    and secure academic data processing within the larger CMS ecosystem.
</MudText>
