@* ===== TECH STACK ===== *@
<MudText Typo="Typo.h4" Class="mt-8 mb-2" Style="font-weight: 700;">
    <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Code" Class="mr-2" Style="vertical-align: middle;" />
    Technology Stack &amp; Frameworks
</MudText>
<MudDivider Class="mb-4" />

<MudGrid Spacing="4" Class="mb-6">
    <MudItem xs="12" sm="6" md="4">
        <MudCard Elevation="2" Style="border-radius: 12px; height: 100%;">
            <MudCardHeader>
                <CardHeaderContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" Color="Color.Primary">.NET 9 &amp; Blazor</MudText>
                </CardHeaderContent>
                <CardHeaderActions>
                    <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Web" Color="Color.Primary" />
                </CardHeaderActions>
            </MudCardHeader>
            <MudCardContent>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                    The application is built on <strong>.NET 9</strong> using the <strong>Blazor</strong> framework in a
                    hybrid Interactive Server + WebAssembly render mode. This allows server-side rendering for initial
                    page loads while enabling rich client-side interactivity.
                </MudText>
            </MudCardContent>
        </MudCard>
    </MudItem>

    <MudItem xs="12" sm="6" md="4">
        <MudCard Elevation="2" Style="border-radius: 12px; height: 100%;">
            <MudCardHeader>
                <CardHeaderContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" Color="Color.Secondary">MudBlazor UI</MudText>
                </CardHeaderContent>
                <CardHeaderActions>
                    <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Palette" Color="Color.Secondary" />
                </CardHeaderActions>
            </MudCardHeader>
            <MudCardContent>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                    The entire user interface is built with <strong>MudBlazor</strong>, a Material Design component
                    library for Blazor. It provides pre-built, responsive, and accessible components like tables,
                    dialogs, forms, navigation drawers, and snackbars.
                </MudText>
            </MudCardContent>
        </MudCard>
    </MudItem>

    <MudItem xs="12" sm="6" md="4">
        <MudCard Elevation="2" Style="border-radius: 12px; height: 100%;">
            <MudCardHeader>
                <CardHeaderContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" Color="Color.Tertiary">Entity Framework Core</MudText>
                </CardHeaderContent>
                <CardHeaderActions>
                    <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Storage" Color="Color.Tertiary" />
                </CardHeaderActions>
            </MudCardHeader>
            <MudCardContent>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                    <strong>Entity Framework Core 9</strong> is used as the ORM (Object-Relational Mapper) that bridges
                    the application code and the database. It supports migrations, LINQ queries, and change tracking
                    for a smooth data-access experience.
                </MudText>
            </MudCardContent>
        </MudCard>
    </MudItem>

    <MudItem xs="12" sm="6" md="4">
        <MudCard Elevation="2" Style="border-radius: 12px; height: 100%;">
            <MudCardHeader>
                <CardHeaderContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" Color="Color.Info">Microsoft SQL Server</MudText>
                </CardHeaderContent>
                <CardHeaderActions>
                    <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Dns" Color="Color.Info" />
                </CardHeaderActions>
            </MudCardHeader>
            <MudCardContent>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                    The back-end database is powered by <strong>Microsoft SQL Server (MSSQL)</strong>. All tables,
                    views, and stored procedures are managed through SSMS 2022, and the application connects via
                    the EF Core SQL Server provider.
                </MudText>
            </MudCardContent>
        </MudCard>
    </MudItem>

    <MudItem xs="12" sm="6" md="4">
        <MudCard Elevation="2" Style="border-radius: 12px; height: 100%;">
            <MudCardHeader>
                <CardHeaderContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" Color="Color.Warning">ASP.NET Identity</MudText>
                </CardHeaderContent>
                <CardHeaderActions>
                    <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Lock" Color="Color.Warning" />
                </CardHeaderActions>
            </MudCardHeader>
            <MudCardContent>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                    Authentication and authorization are handled by <strong>ASP.NET Core Identity</strong>. It provides
                    secure user registration, login, password hashing, role management, and two-factor authentication
                    out of the box.
                </MudText>
            </MudCardContent>
        </MudCard>
    </MudItem>

    <MudItem xs="12" sm="6" md="4">
        <MudCard Elevation="2" Style="border-radius: 12px; height: 100%;">
            <MudCardHeader>
                <CardHeaderContent>
                    <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" Color="Color.Success">C# &amp; Razor</MudText>
                </CardHeaderContent>
                <CardHeaderActions>
                    <MudIcon Icon="@Icons.Material.Filled.Terminal" Color="Color.Success" />
                </CardHeaderActions>
            </MudCardHeader>
            <MudCardContent>
                <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
                    The entire application logic — controllers, services, DTOs, and UI components — is written in
                    <strong>C#</strong> with <strong>Razor</strong> syntax for component templates. The codebase follows
                    a clean layered architecture with shared libraries.
                </MudText>
            </MudCardContent>
        </MudCard>
    </MudItem>
</MudGrid>

